Phase 2-D: Iterative Queue Drain with Per-Op Resilience + Dead-Letter Protection
What: Replace recursive drainQueue with iterative for-of loop that continues on per-operation failure, and add dead-letter protection using the existing retryCount field so permanently unprocessable ops are discarded after MAX_DRAIN_RETRIES attempts.
Design note: The retryCount field already exists on QueuedSaveOperation (set to 0 in queueSave), but drainQueue never uses it. Without dead-letter protection, a permanently failing op causes infinite queue growth and repeated error toasts on every reconnect.
