Phase 2-E: Autosave Stale Closure Fix + Hook Split (75-Line Limit Compliance)
What: Use useRef to always save the latest nodes/edges, avoiding stale closure capture in the debounced save(). Also split useAutosave.ts (currently 138 lines — nearly double the 75-line hook limit) into two focused hooks.
CLAUDE.md compliance: The 75-line hook limit is non-negotiable. useAutosave.ts at 138 lines violates this. Adding ~6 lines of refs would make it worse. The fix is to extract save logic into a separate hook.
Hook split design:
  useSaveCallback.ts (~50 lines): Owns latestNodesRef, latestEdgesRef, latestWorkspaceRef. Exposes a stable save() function. Contains the visibility-change flush effect (flush pending save when tab becomes hidden). Responsibility: "what to save and how."
  useAutosave.ts (~75 lines): Calls useSaveCallback. Handles JSON diffing, debounce scheduling via setTimeout, lastSavedRef tracking, and the isWorkspaceLoading gate. Responsibility: "when to save."
This follows SRP — save logic vs schedule logic are distinct responsibilities.
