Tech debt incurred & resolved:
Incurred: Using refs alongside selectors is a pattern that could confuse future developers.
Resolved: Add a brief doc comment explaining why refs are used: "Refs ensure save() always persists the latest state, avoiding stale closure capture in debounced callbacks." This is a well-known React pattern, not tech debt.
Zustand/ReactFlow safety check: The save callback no longer closes over nodes/edges, which means it won't trigger unnecessary re-creation. The effect still depends on selector values for change detection — this is correct. No "Maximum update depth" risk because save stability improved (fewer re-creations → fewer effect re-runs).
